    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal after replacing brake pads is a common, yet frustrating, issue. It could be a few things, like the pads not bedding in properly, or perhaps the rotors are slightly uneven. A stuck caliper is definitely a possibility, as it can cause uneven pad wear and noise, which is something a mechanic should inspect. Have a shop check the caliper function and ensure the new pads are seated correctly.",
